        <abstract> 
<p>Expresses thanks and pleasure at what GB has said about his book [<hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>] in GB’s [Presidential] Address [to the Linnean Society, 1868, <hi rend="italic">Proc. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> (1868): lvii–c]. "What you say about Pangenesis quite satisfies me".</p> 
            <p>CD discussed "bud-variation" to show that it was an error to believe all variability is due to sexual generation.</p>
        </abstract>
